<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Travel Tips for Visitors to the UK</title>

  <!-- Bootstrap CSS -->
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha1/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">

  <!-- Custom CSS -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="stylesheets/emergency-contacts.css">
</head>

<body>
  <div class="container mt-5">

    <!-- Main Header -->
    <header class="text-center">
      <h1>Travel Tips for Visitors to the UK</h1>
    </header>
    <div class="text-center mb-4">
      <%= link_to image_tag('shield.png', alt: 'Shield Icon', class: 'img-fluid', style: 'max-width: 200px;'), '#travel-tips', class: 'btn btn-link' %>
    </div>

    <!-- Travel Tips Section -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="mt-4">Travel Tips</h2>
      <p>Here are some useful tips for your visit to the UK:</p>

      <!-- Travel Tips List -->
      <ul class="travel-tips list-unstyled">
        <li class="tip-item">
          <strong>Always carry an umbrella</strong>
          <p>The weather can be unpredictable! It's always smart to carry an umbrella just in case.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="tip-item">
          <strong>International calling plan</strong>
          <p>Ensure you have an international calling plan to avoid expensive roaming fees.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="tip-item">
          <strong>Public transport in London</strong>
          <p>Consider getting an Oyster card to easily pay for public transport within London.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="tip-item">
          <strong>Learn basic British phrases</strong>
          <p>Learning a few common British phrases and slang can help you better communicate with locals.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="tip-item">
          <strong>Set emergency contacts in your phone</strong>
          <p>Use "ICE" (In Case of Emergency) in your phone to easily identify emergency contacts.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="tip-item">
          <strong>Use apps to explore new places</strong>
          <p>Apps like Meetup can help you find locals with similar interests to explore with.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="tip-item">
          <strong>Carry British Pounds</strong>
          <p>Carry some British Pounds for small purchases, though contactless payments are widely accepted.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="tip-item">
          <strong>Tipping culture</strong>
          <p>Tipping in restaurants (10-15%) is appreciated but not mandatory.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="tip-item">
          <strong>Respect personal space</strong>
          <p>Personal space is important in the UK, and saying “sorry” is very common.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="tip-item">
          <strong>Driving tips</strong>
          <p>Drive on the left side of the road and be aware of cyclists.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="tip-item">
          <strong>Public toilets</strong>
          <p>Be prepared to pay a small fee for using public toilets, especially in tourist areas.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="tip-item">
          <strong>Dress in layers</strong>
          <p>UK weather can change quickly, so dressing in layers is a good idea.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="tip-item">
          <strong>Get a local SIM card</strong>
          <p>Consider buying a local SIM card to avoid roaming fees.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="tip-item">
          <strong>Use public transport apps</strong>
          <p>Apps like Citymapper or Trainline can help you navigate public transport.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="tip-item">
          <strong>Free museum entry</strong>
          <p>Many UK museums offer free entry. Check out special exhibitions too.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="tip-item">
          <strong>Queuing etiquette</strong>
          <p>Always wait your turn in line (queueing is very important in British culture).</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Emergency Contacts Section -->
    <section class="emergency-contacts mt-5">
      <h2 class="text-center">Emergency Contacts</h2>

      <!-- Emergency Contact Image -->
      <div class="text-center">
        <%= image_tag 'info_icon.png', alt: 'Emergency Contact', class: 'img-fluid mb-3', style: 'max-width: 200px;' %>
      </div>

      <!-- Emergency Numbers List -->
      <ul class="list-group">
        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Emergency Services:</strong> 999</li>
        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Non-Emergency Police:</strong> 101</li>
        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Fire Service:</strong> 999</li>
        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>NHS Non-Emergency:</strong> 111</li>
        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Ambulance Service:</strong> 999</li>
        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Crimestoppers:</strong> 0800 555 111</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="text-center mt-2">
        <strong>Remember to travel safe!</strong>

        <!-- UK Tourism Link -->
        <p class="text-center mt-3">
          <strong>For more information, visit the official UK tourism website:</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="text-center">
          <span>Find more travel tips on this official government site!</span>
        </p>
        <p class="text-center">
          <a href="https://www.visitbritain.com/en" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary">
            <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/a/ae/Flag_of_the_United_Kingdom.svg" alt="UK Flag" style="width: 20px; margin-right: 8px;">
            Visit Britain
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</body>

</html>
